00:18.126 --> 00:22.095
Sophie, wake up.

00:22.097 --> 00:24.631
Wake up, Sophie.

00:24.633 --> 00:27.801
Hi. Come on.

00:27.803 --> 00:29.135
I got a surprise for you.

00:29.137 --> 00:31.137
(laughs)

00:31.139 --> 00:32.856
Come on.

00:32.858 --> 00:35.025
(woman giggles)

00:44.486 --> 00:47.287
Come on.

00:47.289 --> 00:49.039
Daddy!
Daddy!

00:49.041 --> 00:50.907
MAN ON SCREEN (laughing):
Hey.

00:50.909 --> 00:52.792
Hey, kiddos!

00:52.794 --> 00:54.461
Daddy, today's
my hula recital!

00:54.463 --> 00:55.962
Yeah, I can see that.

00:55.964 --> 00:58.498
She hasn't taken it off
all week.

00:58.500 --> 01:00.583
Well, Mommy's gonna
send me a video.

01:00.585 --> 01:02.752
I can't wait to see it.

01:02.754 --> 01:05.672
I wish you could be there.

01:05.674 --> 01:08.642
I know you do, sweetie.
So do I.

01:08.644 --> 01:11.011
And Davey,

01:11.013 --> 01:12.178
you being a good boy?

01:12.180 --> 01:13.596
Yes, sir.

01:13.598 --> 01:14.931
You watch out
for your mom and sister.

01:14.933 --> 01:16.766
Remember, you're the C.O.
while I'm away.

01:16.768 --> 01:18.234
Yes, sir.

01:22.574 --> 01:23.907
I'm gonna need

01:23.909 --> 01:25.108
to talk to Mommy now.

01:25.110 --> 01:26.409
I love you guys.

01:26.411 --> 01:28.361
Bye, Daddy. Love you, Dad.
Bye, Daddy. Love you, Dad...

01:28.363 --> 01:31.281
I may not be able
to call for a few days.

01:31.283 --> 01:32.916
Just don't want you to worry.

01:32.918 --> 01:36.119
Just repeat these words.

01:36.121 --> 01:40.423
“My husband's a badass,
and all will be fine.”

01:43.679 --> 01:45.128
I love you.

01:46.014 --> 01:48.732
I love you, too.

02:11.323 --> 02:13.156
(indistinct radio communication)

02:37.766 --> 02:39.883
WOMAN (over P.A.):
<i>Aloha, parents.</i>

02:39.885 --> 02:41.217
Please take your seats.

02:41.219 --> 02:44.020
The second grade
hula recital is about to begin.

02:44.022 --> 02:46.222
Mahalo and enjoy the show.

02:47.726 --> 02:49.859
It's so exciting.

02:49.861 --> 02:52.028
(applause and cheering)

02:53.815 --> 02:56.733
(whooping, cheers, applause)

02:58.904 --> 03:02.038
♪ ♪

03:06.128 --> 03:08.995
Where's Sophie?

03:08.997 --> 03:10.797
I don't know.

03:10.799 --> 03:12.749
Stay right here, okay?

03:12.751 --> 03:14.667
Excuse me.

03:14.669 --> 03:16.252
<i>Where's Sophie?</i>
<i>Why isn't she on stage?</i>

03:16.254 --> 03:18.004
WOMAN: <i>Angela, we're trying</i>
<i>to find her.</i>

03:18.006 --> 03:19.429
ANGELA: <i>What do you mean “find her”?</i>
<i>Where is she?</i>

03:19.429 --> 03:20.736
We don't know.

03:20.759 --> 03:22.143
TEACHERS: Sophie? Sophie?
Where are you, Sophie?

03:22.144 --> 03:23.843
Why haven't you
been watching her?

03:23.845 --> 03:25.145
TEACHER:
Angela? Angela?

03:25.147 --> 03:27.013
I found this by the back door.

03:27.015 --> 03:28.815
It's Sophie's.

03:28.817 --> 03:30.150
Her father gave it to her.

03:30.152 --> 03:32.352
She would never take it off.

03:36.658 --> 03:38.691
Where's my daughter?

03:38.693 --> 03:42.579
Oh, my God, where's my daughter?

03:42.581 --> 03:46.182
<i>(Hawaii Five-O</i>
theme song plays)

03:46.206 --> 03:50.206
<font color="#00FF00">♪ Hawaii Five-O 5x02 ♪</font>
<font color="#00FFFF">Ka Makuakane</font>
<font color="#00FFFF">(Family Man)</font>
